  "note": "Long, low intensity efforts aren't the only way to build endurance. By incorporating short surges into a steady effort you will increase your oxygen uptake and training stimulus. Completing a low intensity effort with a surge every few minutes should feel comfortable, but the constant change in power and surging, will provide you with big gains in endurance. (by Kevin Poulton)",
